Embakasi East MP has issued a statement moment after his dramatic arrest following a shooting incident at Nairobi’s B-club that left the DJ injured. On his Facebook post, Babu claims that he has been living under the weight of intimidation and threats from his political opponents that want him dead. He goes ahead and says that yesterday was the culmination of the efforts by his enemies when he was surrounded by aggressive men that in turn led to the exchange of gunfire. Babu is likely to spend the weekend at Kilimani police station as he waits to know his fate. Meanwhile Kilimani Police boss Lucas Ogara has said Police are still investigating the circumstance that led to the shooting of the club’s DJ alias DJ Evolve.?